column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Ice out 4/12. First loon back 4/12 second one returned 4/14.  Sunny with a light breeze- no boat traffic.
Overcast with light chop.  Lily pads just breaking the surface- in the shallow bays.
Light chop on the water- a very bright day
Partly cloudy with a light chop on the water.  No boat traffic
Partly sunny- dead calm not a ripple- moderate boat traffic- musky season opened today
Light over cast- small chop on the surface no boat traffic
Several days of rain- but sunny with light waves today- moderate boat traffic. The loons were out with their two chicks.
Heavy boat traffic over the last weekend- sunny with a light chop today.  Resident loons with their chicks out fishing all doing well.
Sunny day- moderate boat traffic and fairly good chop on the surface.
Bright sunny with light breeze- moderate boat traffic
Bright sunshine with small waves- moderate boat traffic.
Sunny with a light breeze out of the southwest- waterskiers out.
Sunny with light waves- moderate boat traffic
Sunny day with fairly heavy chop on the water. Young loons trying out their wings- flight ok landing needs work.
No boat traffic. Algae very heavy along the shore line- large amounts of vegetation floating on the surface.  Submersed bog raised making some bays difficult to navigate
Sunny with a medium breeze. Last weekends musky tournament and Monday's rain has the lake a little turbid.
Sunny with a light breeze- heavy rains last week have raised lake levels
sunny day with light breeze- no boat traffic most of the boats out for the winter
Sunny with light breeze- surface temp 55 degrees. Very windy last week still has lake a little turbit.  Ice off 4/12/06- loons back 4/10/06.
Bright sunshine- moderate wave action- .8 inch of rain the last two days- surface temp 58f.
Several days of rain and heavy Memorial Day boat traffic has the lake quite turib.  Surface temp at 72 degrees.
Bright sun- light wave action. Surface temp 72*
Partly cloudy- moderate west winds- surface temp 74*.  Found Curly-leaf pond weed on 6/6- and Eurasian milfoil on 6/15
Light overcast- with moderate baot traffic- surface temp 76*
Sunny with a light breeze- surface temp at 78*  heavy algae bloom
Sunny with a very light breeze- surface temp 78* 3" of rain since last reading seems to have helped reduce the algae
Partly sunny with a light breeze- surface temp 76*
Sunny with very light breeze    Sunny with light breeze  Sunny with a light breeze- no boat traffic.
Sunny with a  fairly heavy chop on on the water- surface temp at 65.  Loon out with a single chick- second egg unhatched in the nest.
Bright sun- slight breeze with very light wave- and no boat traffic.  Surface temp at 74 degrees.
Partly sunny with a light breeze- very little boat traffic Partly sunny with a light breeze- very little boat traffic.  Surface temp 76 degrees.
Heavy rain and winds two days ago has lake alittle turbid. Partly sunny today with heavy chop .
Heavy rain this week- but partly sunny today with strong north winds producing a heavy chop.  Surface temp at 74 degrees.
Mostly sunny with very light breeze- surface temp at 78 degrees
Sunny with moderate waves- lake very busy today skiers and tubers.  Surface temp at 80 degrees.
Bright sun with very light waves- no boat traffic. Surface temp 72 degrees.
Bright sun- with very little wave action- surface temp 68 degrees.
Sunny with light breeze- very little boat  traffic.  Loon on the nest- two others fishing fishing no the main body.
Partly cloudy today with moderate wave action- sufrace temp at 68 degrees. See both loons on the lake checked the nest found egg shells.

A beautiful day sunny with slight light breeze- surface temp at 71 degrees.  On the sad note the loons have lost their chick- I fear that it may have become dinner for the young eaglet- such is nature's way.
Sunny with very light breeze-little to no boat traffic- surface temp 74 degrees.
Sunny day with very light breeze- little to no boat traffic-  Surface temp at 74 degrees.
Bright sun with no wind- no boat traffic surface temp 75 deg with a heavy algae bloom.
Mostly sunny with very light breeze- surface temp 75 degrees.  Alge very heavy starting to look like pea soup
Memorial Day weekend- very bright day with slight ripple on the surface- moderate boat traffic.  A perfect day.
Sunny day with a very light breeze- surface temp at 64 degrees.
Partly sunny with moderate waves and no boat traffic.  Partly sunny with moderate waves and no boat traffic- surface temp at 70 degrees.
Sunny skies with moderate northwest winds giving light wave action- surface temp 64 degrees
Sunny day with light wind- moderate boat traffic- 2 personal water crafts giving a fair amount of wave action.
Sunny with small waves and no boat traffic.
Slight overcast no wind- the lake is starting to get a algae bloom.
Partly cloudy- no wind and no boat traffic. The adult loons have left the lake only this years chick remains- summer is over.  Surface temp at 68 degrees
Bright sunny day with little to no boat traffic slight breeze.
Memorial Day weekend lake kind of busy- very slight breeze
Several days of rain last week- partly sunny light breeze.
Overcast with about a 10mph wind producing a moderate wave action- no secchi reading just d.o. and temp.
Sunny day with moderate breeze- a couple of boats pulling tubers a few fishermen out.  Very heavy weed growth this year- several species have reached the surface at the twelve to fifteen foot depth.
Partly cloudy today but had heavy rains last evening.
Scattered clouds temperatures expected to reach into the 90's today- very little breeze and no boat traffic at all.
Two days of strong winds have the lake fairly well mixed.
Clear skies with fairly heavy chop on the water.
Lake very busy- skiers- tubers- and fishermen- plus heavy rains the last couple of days has the lake fairly riled.
Clear skies with a moderate chop on the surface.
Partly sunny and a moderate breeze- lake rather busy today skiers and fisherman both.
Sunny day with a light breeze and moderate boat traffic.
Sunny with slight breeze- no boat traffic.
Sunny very light breeze- no boat traffic
Clear skies with a north westerly breeze- recent rains have the lake a little high and slightly riled
Partly cloudy with fairly heavy west wind causing a heavy chop on the surface- with very little boat traffic.
Sunny with stiff breese form the west- Memorial Day- moderate lake use.  Rain last three days.
Sunny with light breeze- heavy rain 2 days before.
Mostly cloudy- alot of boat traffic- rain last night and this morning.
Cloudy with a mild north wind- rain the last three days
